|title=The new sd-bus API of systemd|url=http://0pointer.net/blog/the-new-sd-bus-api-of-systemd.html|date=19 June 2015|accessdate=21 October 2015}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Poettering 2015 q1\">{{cite web|last1=Poettering|first1=Lennart|title=The new sd-bus API of systemd|url=http://0pointer.net/blog/the-new-sd-bus-api-of-systemd.html|date=19 June 2015|accessdate=21 October 2015|quote=\"we are working on moving things to a true user bus, of which there is only one per user on a system, regardless how many times that user happens to log in\"}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Poettering 2015 q2\">{{cite web|last1=Poettering|first1=Lennart|title=The new sd-bus API of systemd|url=http://0pointer.net/blog/the-new-sd-bus-api-of-systemd.html|date=19 June 2015|accessdate=21 October 2015|quote=\"Since systemd's inception it has been the IPC system it exposes its interfaces on.\"}}</ref>\n<!-- ------------ other references ------------ -->\n<ref name=\"gdbus\">{{cite web|title=gdbus|url=https://developer.gnome.org/gio/stable/gdbus.html|website=GNOME developer|accessdate=4 January 2015}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"gdbus2\">{{cite web|title=Migrating to GDBus|url=https://developer.gnome.org/gio/stable/ch35.html|website=GNOME Developer|accessdate=21 October 2015|quote=\"dbus-glib uses the libdbus reference implementation, GDBus doesn't. Instead, it relies on GIO streams as transport layer, and has its own implementation for the D-Bus connection setup and authentication.\"}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"qtdbus\">{{cite web|title=QtDBus module|url=http://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qtdbus-index.html|website=Qt Project|accessdate=1 June 2015}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"dbus-java\">{{cite web|title=DBus-Java Documentation|url=http://dbus.freedesktop.org/doc/dbus-java/|website=FreeDesktop.org|accessdate=4 January 2015}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"polkit doc\">{{cite web|title=Polkit reference manual|url=http://www.freedesktop.org/software/polkit/docs/latest/polkit.8.html|website=FreeDesktop.org|accessdate=3 November 2015}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"dbus 1.0\">{{cite mailing list|mailing-list=dbus|title=[announce] D-Bus 1.0.0 \"Blue Bird\" released|first=John|last=Palmieri|date=9 Nov 2006|url=http://lists.freedesktop.org/archives/dbus/2006-November/006337.html}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"systemd 221\">{{cite mailing list|mailing-list=systemd-devel|title=[ANNOUNCE] systemd v221|first=Lennart|last=Poettering|authorlink=Lennart Poettering|date=19 Jun 2015|url=http://lists.freedesktop.org/archives/systemd-devel/2015-June/033170.html}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.freedesktop.org/Software/dbus D-Bus] home page at Freedesktop.org\n* [http://dbus.freedesktop.org/doc/dbus-specification.html D-Bus specification]\n* [http://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/IntroductionToDBus Introduction to D-Bus] on the Freedesktop.org wiki\n* [http://dbus.freedesktop.org/doc/dbus-tutorial.html D-Bus Tutorial]\n* [https://pythonhosted.org/txdbus/dbus_overview.html DBus Overview]\n\n{{Clear}}\n\n{{Freedesktop.org}}\n{{IPC}}\n\n[[Category:Application layer protocols]]\n[[Category:C++ libraries]]\n[[Category:Free network-related software]]\n[[Category:Freedesktop.org]]\n[[Category:Inter-process communication]]\n[[Category:Remote procedure call]]\n[[Category:Software using the Academic Free License]]\n[[Category:Collabora]]\n", "name_user": "Zyxw", "label": "safe", "comment": "update link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/D-Bus"}
